Package allpeople

Class PersonDirectory

java.lang.Object
allpeople.PersonDirectory
public class PersonDirectory
extends java.lang.Object
This class will represent a person directory of a school. It contains the list of students and the list of faculty members from which we will be able to manipulate and output data as we please.
Since:
: 12/01/2020

    • scheduledStudentsOutput

      public void scheduledStudentsOutput() throws java.lang.Exception
      This method will output the following information to the scheduledStudentsOutput file: 1. Outputs each student's full details (i.e. name, address, contact info) 2. Outputs the courses the student is taking, along with the description of the course 3. Outputs the unique session id of the course the student is in
      Throws:
      java.lang.Exception - : throws an file exception if the file cannot be found

    • sortStudentCourses

      public void sortStudentCourses()
      This method will sort the courses for students. It will look at the list of courses student has and sees if the course they chose is going to be taught or not. If it is taught and they are signed up it will go ahead and check if the session the student is in is going to be scheduled. If they do not qualify for those conditions the student will be taken out of that course.

    • sortFacultyCourses

      public void sortFacultyCourses()
      This method will sort the courses for each faculty. It will go through each faculty in the list and will check if a course is scheduled or not. If it is scheduled the course stands inside the faculty's data or else the course will be deleted from the faculy's course list.

    • sortFacultySessions

      public void sortFacultySessions()
      This method will sort the session's of a course for each faculty. It will check if a certain session inside the course is not going to be scheduled because of the minimum student requirement not being met. If the session is not scheduled then the course session will be deleted from the faculty's list of courses and sessions

    • unscheduledStudentsOutput

      public void unscheduledStudentsOutput() throws java.lang.Exception

      Throws:
      java.lang.Exception - : throws an file exception if the file cannot be found

    • facultyOutput

      public void facultyOutput() throws java.lang.Exception
      This method will print the following information to FacultyOutput.txt text file: 1) Details of each faculty member (i.e. Name, address, contact info, etc) 2) Full course detail of each course along with the session they are scheduled in 3) Session ID and number of students in each session
      Throws:
      java.lang.Exception - : File exceptions
